OL,4,COffa's Dyke: Monument damaged by
OL,5,C'centuries of benign neglect'
OL,6, The United Kingdom's longest ancient
OL,7, monument has been damaged by "centuries
OL,8, of gradual benign neglect", says an
OL,9, association fighting to preserve it.
OL,11,FA fund has started to help preserve the
OL,12,F8th Century Offa's Dyke earthwork.
OL,14,FOffa's Dyke has "a lot of catching up
OL,15,Fto do" compared with other monuments
OL,16,Flike Hadrian's Wall and Stonehenge,
OL,17,Faccording to its association chairman.
OL,19,FDave McGlade said the 177 mile (285 km)
OL,20,Fmonument on the Wales-England border is
OL,21,Fa "sensitive archaeological landscape."
